=David Dean Shulman |author3=Sanjay Subrahmanyam|title= Symbols of substance: court and state in N\u0101yaka Period Tamilnadu|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=1992|isbn=0-19-563021-1}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=V5khtVz0yIgC&pg=PA9&lpg=PA9&dq=harihara+bukka+golla|title=Cyclic Tables of Hindu and Mahomedan Chronology, Regarding the History of the Telugu and Kannadi Countries to which are Added the Genealogies of Particular Hindu Families, with Essays on Various Matters of Enquiry|last=Brown|first=Charles Philip|date=1994|publisher=Asian Educational Services|isbn=978-81-206-0929-7|language=en}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=IS1uAAAAMAAJ|title=Vijayanagar: As Seen by Domingos Paes and Fernao Nuniz (16th Century Portuguese Chroniclers and Others)|last=Sewell|first=Robert|date=1999|publisher=National Book Trust, India|isbn=978-81-237-2658-8|language=en}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Crawford |first1=Michael H |last2=Reddy |first2=B. Mohan |last3=Martinez-Laso |first3=Jorge |last4=Mack |first4=Steven J |last5=Erlich |first5=Henry A |title=Genetic variation among the Golla pastoral caste subdivisions of Andhra Pradesh, India, according to the HLA system |journal=Human Immunology |date=1 September 2001 |volume=62 |issue=9 |pages=1031\u20131041 |doi=10.1016/S0198-8859(01)00312-3 |pmid=11543904 }}\n* {{Cite journal|last=Bheenaveni|first=Ram|title=Golla+Kuruma=Yadav (Gollakurumalu Okkate)|url=https://www.academia.edu/4541427|language=en}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Golla}}\n[[Category:Telugu society]]\n[[Category:Hindu communities]]\n[[Category:Social groups of Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Agricultural castes]]\n\n[[hi:\u092f\u093e\u0926\u0935]]\n[[kn:\u0c97\u0cca\u0cb2\u0ccd\u0cb2]]\n[[ta:\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe]]\n[[te:\u0c17\u0c4a\u0c32\u0c4d\u0c32 \u0c35\u0c3e\u0c30\u0c41]]\n", "name_user": "Sathyanarayana naidu", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golla_(caste)"}
{"title_page": "Ra\u00fal Hirales Jr.", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican boxer}}\n{{spanish name 2|Hirales|Cuevas}}\n{{Infobox boxer|name= Ra\u00fal Hirales\n|image=\n|realname          = Ra\u00fal Benjamin Hirales Cuevas\n|nickname          = Raul Hirales Jr.\n|weight            = [[Featherweight]]<br/>[[Super bantamweight]]\n|height            = 5 ft 7 in (173 cm)\n|reach             = 70 in (178 cm)\n|nationality       = Mexican\n|birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1984|1|25}}\n|birth_place       = [[La Paz, Baja California Sur]], Mexico\n|style             = [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n|total             = 29\n|wins              = 22\n|KO                = 11\n|losses            = 6\n|draws             = 1\n|no contests       = 0\n}}\n'''Ra\u00fal Benjamin Hirales Cuevas''' (born January 25, 1984) is Mexican professional [[Boxing|boxer]] in the [[Super Bantamweight]] division.<ref>http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?cat=boxer&human_id=388344</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nOn January 28, 2011 Hirales beat the veteran [[Charles Huerta]] at the Four Points Sheraton Hotel in [[San Diego, California]]. The bout was televised by [[Telefutura]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=614853</ref>\n\nIn his next fight on May 26, 2012, Hirales traveled to [[Nottingham, UK]], to face fellow unbeaten fighter, [[Carl Frampton]] for the vacant IBF Inter-Continental Super Bantamweight Title \non the undercard of [[Carl Froch vs. Lucian Bute]]. He lost the bout by unanimous decision.\n\nIn May 2015, Hirales lost on points to Jessie Magdaleno at the Chelsea Ballroom, [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], USA.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{boxrec|id=388344}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hirales, Raul Jr.}}\n[[Category:Boxers from Baja California Sur]]\n[[Category:People from La Paz, Baja California Sur]]\n[[Category:Super-bantamweight boxers]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mexican male boxers]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in boxing]]\n\n\n{{Mexico-boxing-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mexican boxer}}\n{{spanish name 2|Hirales|Cuevas}}\n{{Infobox boxer|name= Ra\u00fal Hirales\n|image=\n|realname          = Ra\u00fal Benjamin Hirales Cuevas\n|nickname          = Raul Hirales Jr.\n|weight            = [[Featherweight]]<br/>[[Super bantamweight]]\n|height            = 5 ft 7 in (173 cm)\n|reach             = 70 in (178 cm)\n|nationality       = Mexican\n|birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1984|1|25}}\n|birth_place       = [[La Paz, Baja California Sur]], Mexico\n|style             = [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n|total             = 29\n|wins              = 22\n|KO                = 11\n|losses            = 6\n|draws             = 1\n|no contests       = 0\n}}\n'''Ra\u00fal Benjamin Hirales Cuevas''' (born January 25, 1984) is Mexican professional [[Boxing|boxer]] in the [[Super Bantamweight]] division.<ref>http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?cat=boxer&human_id=388344</ref>\n\n==Professional career==\nOn January 28, 2011 Hirales beat the veteran [[Charles Huerta]] at the Four Points Sheraton Hotel in [[San Diego, California]]. The bout was televised by [[Telefutura]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=614853</ref>\n\nIn his next fight on May 26, 2012, Hirales traveled to [[Nottingham, UK]], to face fellow unbeaten fighter, [[Carl Frampton]] for the vacant IBF Inter-Continental Super Bantamweight Title \non the undercard of [[Carl Froch vs. Lucian Bute]]. He lost the bout by unanimous decision.\n\nIn May 2015, Hirales lost on points to Jessie Magdaleno at the Chelsea Ballroom, [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], USA.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{boxrec|id=388344}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hirales, Raul Jr.}}\n[[Category:Boxers from Baja California Sur]]\n[[Category:People from La Paz, Baja California Sur]]\n[[Category:Super-bantamweight boxers]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mexican male 